Author: Osamu Miyawaki <omiyawaki@icloud.com>
Date:   Wed Aug 6 15:42:49 2025 -0400

    fix: Implement web-matching selective border pattern for navbox tables
    
    Replace full borders with selective border sides to eliminate inset effect
    and match the desktop wiki's proven navbox design. After investigating
    the actual HTML/CSS from oldschool.runescape.wiki, discovered that the
    web version uses selective borders rather than full borders.
    
    Key changes:
    - Group titles: Right + bottom borders only (border-width: 0 1px 1px 0)
    - Lists: Bottom border only (border-bottom: 1px solid)
    - Row separators: Top border on 2nd+ rows (tr:nth-child(n+2))
    - Apply same pattern to both main navbox and nested subgroups
    
    This eliminates the inset effect by preventing border overlap while
    creating a clean grid that matches the desktop experience exactly.
